definition.value: This is an AE which is a major cause of vision loss and impairment and a common underlying mechanism associated with diseases such as glaucoma, diabetic retinopathy, and central retinal artery occlusion.
This is an AE which is a retinal disease often accompanied by migraine headache and typically affects only one eye.
This is an AE which occurs when fluid and protein deposits collect on or under the macula of the eye (a yellow central area of the retina) and causes it to thicken and swell (edema).

This is an AE which is a pale color of the skin that can be caused by illness, emotional shock or stress, stimulant use, or anemia, and is the result of a reduced amount of oxyhaemoglobin and may also be visible as pallor of the conjunctivae of the eyes on physical examination.

This is an AE which is a relatively novel concept describing a phenotype characterized by attenuation of the choriocapillaris overlying dilated choroidal veins, and associated with progressive retinal pigment epithelium dysfunction and neovascularization.
This is an AE which is confined to inner retinal layers .
This is an AE which is the constellation of ocular signs and symptoms secondary to severe, chronic arterial hypoperfusion to the eye.

This is an AE which is inflammation of the vascular branches of the retinal artery, caused either by primary ocular disease processes, or as a specific presentation of any systemic form of vasculitis such as Behçet's disease, sarcoidosis, multiple sclerosis, or any form of systemic necrotizing vasculitis such as temporal arteritis, polyarteritis nodosa, and granulomatosis with polyangiitis, or due to lupus erythematosus, or rheumatoid arthritis.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the retina in the eye, which can permanently damage the retina and lead to blindness.
This is an AE which is a genetic disorder of the eyes that causes loss of vision and symptoms include trouble seeing at night and decreased peripheral vision (side vision).
This is an AE which is a rare disease that implies involvement of Herpesviridae, a family of double-stranded DNA viruses characterised by latency within the host's cells after primary infection.
This is an AE which is an eye disease characterized by the abnormal splitting of the retina's neurosensory layers, usually in the outer plexiform layer.
This is an AE which typically presents with the perception of light flashes, floaters, or a "dark curtain."

This is an AE which with hypertensive choroidopathy presented with choroidal thickening that decreased after resolution, but the residual flow defects observed in the choriocapillaris on OCTA confirmed the long-hypothesized notion that ischemia is a mechanism underlying hypertensive choroidopathy.
This is an AE which is a result of a wound healing response that follows choroidal neovascularization in neovascular age-related macular degeneration (nAMD).

This is an AE which observed in association with choroidal neovascularization and to distinguish SHE from other forms of subretinal hyperreflective material (SHM) seen in patients with age-related macular degeneration and other macular disorders.
This is an AE which an anomalous posterior vitreous detachment (APVD) with persistant symptomatic vitreoretinal adhesion is seen.
This is an AE which is a rare retinal condition that features the sudden onset of bilateral central scotomata, which may be preceded by a viral prodrome in some patients.

label.value: acute zonal occult outer retinopathy AE

definition.value: This is an AE which is an inflammatory retinopathy in the category of white dot syndromes typified by acute loss of one or more zones of outer retinal function associated with photopsia, minimal funduscopic changes and abnormal electroretinography findings.
This is an AE which is a rare disease in which the patient's immune system attacks proteins in the retina, leading to loss of eyesight.
This is an AE which can be partially compensated by increased use of peripheral vision.
This is an AE which is the partial or complete wasting away of a part of the chorioretinal body.
This is an AE which is the vascular layer of the eye, containing connective tissues, and lying between the retina and the sclera that is gets disorder.
This is an AE which is an area of fibrous tissue that replaces normal chorioretinal skin after an injury.
This is an AE which is an inflammation of the choroid (thin pigmented vascular coat of the eye) and retina of the eye.

This is an AE which is a posterior segment disease characterized by localized and limited serous detachments of the neurosensory retina often associated with focal detachments of an altered retinal pigment epithelium.
This is an AE which is an impairment of the sense of vision.
This is an AE which refers to a risk for myopia may be inherited from one's parents.
This is an AE which is a medical term for seeing everything tinted with blue.
This is an AE which is an inflammation of the choroid (thin pigmented vascular coat of the eye) and retina of the eye caused by cytomegalovirus .
This is an AE which is a medical condition in which damage occurs to the retina due to diabetes mellitus.
This is an AE which is the simultaneous perception of two images of a single object that may be displaced horizontally or vertically in relation to each other.
This is an AE which is a lack of coordination of movement typified by the undershoot or overshoot of intended position with the hand, arm, leg, or eye. It is a type of ataxia.
This is an AE which is a neuropsychological condition that causes a distortion of perception.
This is an AE which is less common but nonetheless a possible reason as to why a patient may fail the 4 PRT.
This is an AE which may be a manifestation of a variety of isolated ocular or systemic diseases in children.
This is an AE which is a visual disturbance in which objects appear with a red hue, is a recognized phenomenon after surgical excision of the natural lens.
This is an AE which is sometimes visible deposits within the eye's vitreous humour ("the vitreous"), which is normally transparent, or between the vitreous and retina.
This is an AE which is a visual disturbance in which objects in the visual field appear to oscillate.
This is an AE which is the phenomenon of seeing light without light entering the eye.
This is an AE which is a scratch to the surface of the cornea of the eye.
This is an AE which is a collection of pus that has built up within the tissue of the corneal.
This is an AE which is severe enough to require corneal transplantation is a rare complication of uveitis.
This is an AE which is deterioration in the medical sense on the corneal.
This is an AE which is the transparent front part of the eye that covers the iris, pupil, and anterior chamber.

This is an AE which refers to anything that interferes with the cornea's stromal architecture, contributes to blood vessel migration, increases corneal pigmentation, or predisposes to corneal edema, disrupts the corneas transparency.
This is an AE which is a group of rare hereditary disorders characterised by bilateral abnormal deposition of substances in the transparent front part of the eye called the cornea.
This is an AE which is a single layer of endothelial cells on the inner surface of the cornea.

This is an AE which is made up of epithelial tissue and covers the front of the cornea and acts as a barrier to protect the cornea, resisting the free flow of fluids from the tears, and prevents bacteria from entering the epithelium and corneal stroma.
This is an AE which is a disorder of the eyes characterized by the failure of the cornea's outermost layer of epithelial cells to attach to the underlying basement membrane (Bowman's layer).
